<p>This section covers the inference system in GigaCheck, which provides th=
e interface for running predictions on text using trained models. The infer=
ence system supports two distinct modes: <strong>classification</strong> (d=
ocument-level human/AI detection) and <strong>detection</strong> (character=
-level interval localization of AI-generated content).</p>
<p>The inference system is built around the <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#=
e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before=
:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">MistralDetector</code> unified i=
nterface that abstracts the underlying model architectures and provides a c=
onsistent prediction API. For detailed instructions on running inference th=
rough the command-line interface, see <a href=3D"https://deepwiki.com/ai-fo=
rever/gigacheck/6.1-running-inference" class=3D"text-neutral-300 hover:text=
-neutral-200 hover:underline">Running Inference</a>. For programmatic usage=
 and API details, see <a href=3D"https://deepwiki.com/ai-forever/gigacheck/=
6.2-mistraldetector-api" class=3D"text-neutral-300 hover:text-neutral-200 h=
over:underline">MistralDetector API</a>.</p>
