<p><strong>Diagram: Inference System Flow</strong></p>
<p>The inference pipeline consists of four layers:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Entry Points</strong>: Users interact through either the CLI sc=
ript (<code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text=
-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]=
/30">inference.py</code>) or the programmatic <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-=
[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] befo=
re:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">MistralDetector</code> class</=
li>
<li><strong>Model Loading Layer</strong>: Detects task type from model conf=
iguration and initializes the appropriate architecture</li>
<li><strong>Processing Pipeline</strong>: Tokenizes input text and performs=
 forward pass through the model</li>
<li><strong>Output Layer</strong>: Formats predictions according to task ty=
pe (classification labels or detection intervals)</li>
</ol>
