<p><strong>Diagram: Model Loading Process</strong></p>
<p>The model loading process follows these steps:</p>
<ol>
<li><strong>Configuration Loading</strong>: Reads <code class=3D"rounded-sm=
 bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] =
before:hidden after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">config.json</code> to dete=
rmine model architecture, task type, and hyperparameters</li>
<li><strong>Model Initialization</strong>: Creates model instance based on =
configuration (classification or detection variant)</li>
<li><strong>Weight Loading</strong>: Loads trained parameters from checkpoi=
nt files (supports both <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e5] px-[0.25rem]=
 py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidden after:hidden=
 dark:bg-[#484848]/30">.bin</code> and <code class=3D"rounded-sm bg-[#e5e5e=
5] px-[0.25rem] py-[0.20rem] text-xs font-normal leading-[15px] before:hidd=
en after:hidden dark:bg-[#484848]/30">.safetensors</code> formats)</li>
<li><strong>Tokenizer Loading</strong>: Initializes the Mistral tokenizer w=
ith proper special tokens and padding configuration</li>
</ol>
<p>For classification models, if LoRA adapters were used during training, t=
he weights should be merged before inference using the merge script describ=
ed in <a href=3D"https://deepwiki.com/ai-forever/gigacheck/4.1-classificati=
on-model-training" class=3D"text-neutral-300 hover:text-neutral-200 hover:u=
nderline">Classification Model Training</a>. The detection models do not us=
e LoRA and can be loaded directly.</p>
